The paper deals with the problem of single image 3D model retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The approach proposed in the paper involves establishing a common low-level representation, which is a fundamental problem in machine learning (LG). The paper also involves the use of synthetic data, which is a common technique in multimedia (MM) research. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of pose estimation, which is a common problem in robotics (RO) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.GR, and cs.LG, followed by cs.MM and cs.RO.
